SIMPLE: symposiac
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Symposiac
<hw>Sym*po"si*ac</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>symposiacus</ets>, Gr. <?/.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to
compotations and merrymaking; happening where company is drinking
together; <as>as, <ex>symposiac</ex> meetings</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Symposiac</qex> disputations amongst my acquaintance.</q>
<rj><qau>Arbuthnot.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Symposiac</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Symposiac
<hw>Sym*po"si*ac</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A conference or conversation
of philosophers at a banquet; hence, any similar gathering.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Symposiarch</ent>⟦br⟧
